  "body": "### Description\r\n**NOTE: This issue DOES NOT address the `compile` dependency configuration deprecation as discussed in the Additional Information section. It only proposes the required changes for each sub-project to be buildable independently.**\r\n\r\nA number of gradle build errors occur when building subprojects independently. (i.e. `./gradlew :[project_path]:build`):\r\n\r\n```\r\n* What went wrong:\r\nA problem occurred evaluating project ':[project_path]'.\r\n> Cannot change dependencies of configuration ':[project_path]:compile' after it has been included in dependency resolution.\r\n```\r\n- ^ Occurs In:\r\n  - :ethereum:datastructures\r\n  - :networking:p2p\r\n  - :proto\r\n  - :util\r\n  - :validator:coordinator\r\n\r\n```\r\n> Task :validator:client:compileJava FAILED\r\n...\r\nerror: package com.google.protobuf does not exist\r\nerror: package io.grpc does not exist\r\n...\r\n```\r\n- ^ Occurs In:\r\n  - :validator:client\r\n  - :validator:coordinator\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* Sub-Projects should be able to be built independently, without relying on dependencies being on the classpath from other modules. In addition, projects should not attempt to change dependencies during the compile step after dependency resolution has completed.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\n1. `./gradlew :validator:client:clean build -x test`\r\n2. `./gradlew :validator:coordinator:clean build -x test`\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\nThe Gradle `compile` dependency configuration is deprecated, and should be substituted for `implementation` or `compileOnly`, where appropriate.\r\nhttps://docs.gradle.org/current/userguide/java_plugin.html#tab:configurations",
